When the eras and civ switching were announced before C7's release I was shocked and horrified. I have played all civ games since the early 90s, and I always did it for immersion: to build a (single) culture to last six millenia. I was worried the civ switches would take away all of my fun. Well, the system works surprisingly well, in practice. My wife and I both like it.

There are some issues though. The ancient and exploration eras are great - the modern one feels like a chore though. I was ok with it for some 300 hours (as in, for 300 hours of game after game in all three eras), but then something snapped in me and I can no longer finish the game in the modern era. I know I will win - it's just that getting there is not fun. There are rumors the developers may allow skipping eras in a future update. I would love that.

Still, if you're not too different from my wife and I, you should get your money's worth from Civ 7.

Graphics are great (8/10, IMO), the music, too. Gameplay is 10/10 in the ancient era 8/10 in the exploration era, and 5/10 tops in the modern era. There is a wide range of civs and leaders to choose from. There are monthly updates, and also dozens of very good mods.

