@elemcee - Yes -- stropping it the final stage in sharpening. I was expecting someone to object to the clue, because the primary function of stropping is to remove any microscopic burs that remain after the actual sharpening process. It doesn't really sharpen the blade. Of course, you can consider stropping to be a part of the overall sharpening process. 

Strop blocks are used for honing things like plane blades, chisels, and the like. I can't imagine what it would be like to strop the blade of a plane on a belt! You need a relatively rigid and FLAT stropping surface for this task. 

Good for you for being open to learning things you don't already know. That's one of the things I like about crosswords (and the column!), learning new stuff. So many people seem to dislike learning new things. I think there has to be at least one entry I'm not familiar with in just about every puzzle -- even Mondays. It doesn't make me hate the puzzle. Quite the opposite.

